# .easignore — files EAS Build excludes from the uploaded project archive.
#
# The Expo mobile app only needs: root config (app.json/eas.json/package*.json/
# babel/metro/tsconfig), index.js, App.js, src/, shared/, and assets/. Everything
# below is dev tooling, tests, docs, or the sibling web/admin/Supabase projects —
# none of which are used to build the app. Excluding them cut the upload from
# ~1.1 GB to a small fraction and makes builds noticeably faster.
#
# NOTE: when a .easignore exists it takes precedence over .gitignore for the EAS
# upload, so the .gitignore patterns are re-listed here (otherwise node_modules,
# build output, and secrets would be re-included).

# --- mirror of .gitignore (keep excluded) ---
node_modules/
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
expo-env.d.ts
.kotlin/
*.orig.*
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision
.metro-health-check*
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*
.DS_Store
*.pem
.env*.local
*.tsbuildinfo
/ios
/android
supabase/.temp/
.vercel
.env*

# --- sibling apps + backend (not needed to build the mobile app) ---
web/
admin/
supabase/

# --- dev tooling / tests / docs / CI ---
__tests__/
scripts/
.github/
.claude/
.vscode/
*.md
